furnish /ˈfɜːnɪʃ/

(furnishing,furnished,furnishes) 

1. V-T If you furnish a room or building, you put furniture and furnishings into it. 装潢; 布置 (房间、建筑物) 

例： Many proprietors try to furnish their hotels with antiques. 许多企业主尽可能用古董装饰他们的旅馆。 

2. V-T If you furnish someone with something, you provide or supply it. 提供 [正式] 

例： They'll be able to furnish you with the rest of the details. 他们将能够给你提供其余的细节。

</div>

